@NODE Err2 "Fuck"

@{bg highlight}INFO:@{bg back}
-----

It could be, that this version does not work
under ECS-Amigas without Graphiccards! 



@{bg highlight}Changes to V1.01 - AmiNet version@{bg back}

- Faster filter/converter code... 

- Removed BUG (Aaarghh) from the Toolbox...

  When the toolbox was on and you type j or n
  the program quits...  (Fuck)

@{bg highlight}Changes to V1.10@{bg back}

- Finished Word8 filter.

- Faster filters for Word7 and Word8

- RTF filter

- ANSI filter

@{bg highlight}Changes to V1.11@{bg back}

- Added Clipboard to TLNG

- Added RexxPort

- Added Upper and LowerCase

@{bg highlight}Changes to V1.12@{bg back}

- @{bg highlight}Fixed locale problem@{bg back}

  TLNG started only with the german locales...

  !Thanks to Joe Solinsky for the bug report!

- Added Preferences to the menu

  Now you can select the pathes/files for:

  Viewer,Viewer (PPacker),Helpguide and Rexxmodules.

- Fixed Help menuitem (see above)

- Fixed Load Picture and Picture(PP) menuitems (see above)

- Fixed Lower/Uppercase

- Added empty Rexx menuitems for users...

@{bg highlight}Changes to V1.13-15@{bg back}

- Added Word6 for MAC filter

- Added "Find classes" to the converter module

- Changed the menu "Converter"

  The subitem "Word 6-8 & Amiga" will replace all
  old subitems of the Word and the Amiga filters.
 
  If you don`t know which kind your document is 
  try first this menuitem.

  If the class/datatype is not supported it will not convert it.

  Supported types are: Word6 (WIN/MAC), Word7 & 8 (WIN), 
                       FinalWriter (5&97), WordWorth & AmiWriter. 

  For all other types you still must use the other subitems, coz
  i didn`t have for these modules text examples to get the right
  type of file. (Like WPerfect,Word for Dos etc.)

- Changed Save menu

- Menus now font sensetive

- Changed some requesters and the editor window to be
  compatible to VisualPrefs

  Thanks to Marko Seppänen for the bug report

- Removed very ugly bug from converting documents. (English locale only)

  I forgot to set a buffer and with no buffer TLNG quits.

  Thanks to Robin Brookes for the bug report.

@{bg highlight}Changes to V1.16@{bg back}

- Add "Set Editorfont" to the menu.

  At the start TLNG will read your fonts.prefs if the selected font
  is not 11pt and not proportional it will change to Topaz 11.
  With the new menuitem you could change this to a font you like,
  with the limitations above. You should select f.e. XEN or a font
  from the ThinXXX family (f.e Thin711).

- Finished filters for WordPerfect5 DOS and 5.x.
  
  If you found some Ä`s at the text these are only some textfunctions
  like bold, i can`t remove this coz otherwise i will get trouble
  with the german version...

- Renamed meunitem Word 6-8 & Amiga to PC & Amiga.

  Supported types are: Word6 (WIN/MAC), Word7 & 8 (WIN), WordPerfect
                       5.0 Dos & 5.x, FinalWriter (5&97), WordWorth 
                       and AmiWriter. 

@{bg highlight}Changes to V1.20-2x@{bg back}

- New Interface

- New functions

- Clock module

- Font module
  Now you can change the font and the size for the editor...

- New SysInfo module

- Now you can change the Editor background color

- Locales
  It is now really easy to create a new language for the TLNG2
  Just edit/change the file TLNG/Locale/English. 
  Don`t edit the German locale!

- New Palette module

- New Search Requester 

- New Search&Replace Requester

- New internal WWorth Rexx module

- Changed the Rexx User menus.
  The selected rexx script will placed at the menu...

@{bg highlight}Changes to V2.0 Beta5@{bg back}

- Added new menuitem: Icon Help
  Enable or disable the help for the icon buttons.

- Fixed some layout problems when using VisualPrefs!

- Fixed Search bug

- Added Line counter

- Changed the max. buffer for the converter modules.

- Locale support finished!

- some internal code changes...

- Removed some unused code...

@{bg highlight}Changes to V2.0 Beta6@{bg back}

- New Palette modul

  This will replace the menuitems: Editor-/Fontcolors

  Following colors can be changed:
  Editorbackground, Editorfont, Highlightcolor and
  the TLNG background..

- Search changed... (word will be marked)

- Changed the position of the clock.

- New menuitem: Refresh

  You will need this item, if you changed the TLNG background.

- New menuitem: Remove HTML code

  This will remove all(?) HTML codes from the text.

- New menuitem: HTML/GFX to PGS3

  You can send the Text & GFX to PageStream3.

  It is still under construction!!! 

  Pagestream must be running. An empty document must be open and
  the cursorposition must be set, if not only the graphics will
  be inserted...

- Bug removed from FinalWriter.rexx
  
- Cut&Paste bug removed!

- Some changes made on marking the text

- ScreenMode

  If you get problems with the selected screenmode, delete the
  file TLNG.screen...

- WWorth import filter

- New Iconhelp (Bubblehelp)

@{bg highlight}Changes to V2.0 Beta7@{bg back}

- WordWorth7 Export Filter

  This will save your document as WordWorth7 document!

  I don`t know if this filter is working with older versions
  of WWorth, if so please let me know...

@{bg highlight}Changes to V2.0 Beta8@{bg back}

- Changes on "Remove HTML code"

- Changes on "Crypt Text"

  First you must type an password for crypting the document...

  For uncrypting the the document, you will need this password...

and some other things...

@{bg highlight}Changes to V2.0 Beta9@{bg back}

- Changed Code and the Rexx module for sending text to FW97.

- Removed bug form "Mark all" (COPY)
  Didn`t work with the clipboard.

- Icon Prefs.
  
  You can use now different icons for the TLNG.
  The size of the new icons must be 21x18

- HTML/GFX to FinalWriter. (Test)

  This will send a loaded HTLM document with layout to FW97.
  -Head,title,bold,italic,underline,center,left and right are
   working.
  -The graphic import is not finished yet, so not all pictures
   will be loaded and the position of the pictures is not working
   now...
  
- CHANGED KEYCODES!!!

  THERE IS A KEYFILE ON SOME FTP SITEZ!
  DON`T TRY THIS KEYFILE WITH THIS VERSION!

  W A R N I N G
  =============
  
  YOU COULD LOST SOME DATA ON YOUR BOOTPATITION!!!

@{bg highlight}Changes to V2.0 Beta10@{bg back}

- Changed internal code... (What ever it is...)

- PGS/FW7 Rexx-Export code changed.

- Changed some Rexxscripts.

- Removed bug from "Load as HEX".

  The program quits if nothing was selected.

- New "Load text" code.

- Changed the PREFS code.

- Changed the position of the filerequesters.

- Danish locale (thanks to Viggo Hinrichsen)

@{bg highlight}Changes to V2.0 Beta11@{bg back}

- ScreenRequester Bug.

@{bg highlight}Changes to V2.0 Beta12@{bg back}

- Fontrequester Bug.

- Word7&8 MAC Filter

- Own Screencolors

- Icons can have now up to 32 colors...
  The screencolor get the color information
  from the first loaded icon (Load).

- The Color and the Fontrequester using now
  the selected language.

- Rexxscript: SendtoYAM

  Sends the Text from TLNG to YAM as a new mail!
  YAM must be running...

- Shell-Syntax: TextLoaderNG (filename)

  You can load now an text when you starting the
  program.

  Supported formats are:

  Text,ASCII,Word6-8,FinalWriter97,WordWorth7,
  AmiWriter,WordPerfect5
  
  Textloader ? shows the syntax.

- Some icons using now menus.

- Changed Search&Replace Requester for smaller
  fonts.

@{bg highlight}Changes to V2.x@{bg back}

-------------------------------------------------------
Known bugs Version 2.20:

- HTML removes not all code from the loaded document.

- RexxManager will crash TLNG when you use a wrong
  command. (This is not a bug)
-------------------------------------------------------

- New code for Load!

  Now you can load all files accept "Form-files" like
  Wordworth with the normal "Load" menu entry.
  Almost all unreadable letters will eliminated from
  the textfile... (try a word document...)

- New HTML-Remove code

- New locale code

- New Colormode (32+ Colors)

- New Icon code

  Icons(Brushes) could have now 32 colors...

  TLNG gets now the colors from the first Icon (Laden/Load)
  (Icon Prefs/Einstellungen)

  If you want to use your own colors (f.e. the colors 
  from your Workbench) you must use an program like 
  DPaint,PPaint etc.  

  Your Workbench colors will be reset after quitting
  TLNG!

- Remove Bug from Icon-Help (->Load)

- Modes directory!

  There are some screen modes created on my computer,
  if you have problems to find the right mode, you should
  rename a file from this directory to TLNG.screen and
  copy it to the prefs directory...
 
- THERE IS STILL A BUTTON TO STOP CONVERTING FILES!!!
  (pls. read the old guide for more informtion which button
   it is!!!)

- New Colorrequester

- Color & Fontrequester

  Colorrequester and Fontrequester using now the selected
  Language (Deutsch,English,France,Italiano and Danish).

- @{bg highlight}Rexxscript: SendtoYAM@{bg back}

  The text will be send to YAM as a new Mail!
  YAM must be open! 
  (Maybe it works if a ASSIGN for YAM exists!? - not tested!)

- @{bg highlight}Rexxscript: SendYAM2TLNG@{bg back}

  YAM mail will be sent to TLNG...

  1. Choose the Mail you want (select only the mail)
  2. Select from the menu Scripts the Select script
     menu and select YAN2TLNG.

  If the mail was crypted, cut the header the end
  of the mail (...or all readable letters) or try
  the Rexx-command RemoveHdr...

- Word8 MAC Filter

- Search and Replace Requester can use now fonts < 11.


- Some Icons using now an Menu.
  Menuhandling: Left Mousebutton  = open Menu
                Right Mousebutton = close Menu, or you wait 10 sec.

- @{bg highlight}Shell-Syntax: TextLoaderNG (Name)@{bg back}

  Now you can load a text with the shell,
  (f.e. TextLoaderNG s:Startup-Sequence)

  or with Opus.
  Opus-Button: TextLoaderNG:TextLoaderNG {F}
 
  Formats:
  --------
  
  Text,ASCII,Word6-8,FinalWriter97,WordWorth7,AmiWriter,WordPerfect5
  
  TextLoaderNG ? will give you the syntax.

- New Search&Replace requester

- Rexxport for the TLNG

  Rexxaddres=TextLoaderNG_IN

  There are only some commands to make it really
  easy....

  Commands:

  OPEN      = Load a Ascii text file
  OPENTXT   = Load a text file
  SAVE      = Save the Text as ASCII
  MARKAll   = mark the Text
  UNMARK    = unmark Text
  COPY      = copy marked Text
  PASTE     = insert Text (Clipboard)
  CUT       = cut/delete Text
  HEX       = load Text as HEX Text
  QUIT      = Quit TLNG 
  PCAMI     = load PC/Amiga Document
  CRYPT     = Crypt Text
  UNCRYPT   = Uncrypt the Text
  TEXTSTART = Start of Document
  TEXTEND   = End of Document
  VERSION   = hmm...
  OPENFILE  = Open an file  (f.e. OPENFILE "S:Startup-Sequence")  
  DOWN      = 1 line down
  UP        = 1 line up
  RTN       = 1 new line / Return
  ANSI      = Load a ANSI-Text and remove the ANSI-Code.
  RTF       = Load a RTF-Text
  INSERT    = Inserts a new Text to the old one.
  DATE      = Insert the date.
  TIME      = Insert the time.
  DO_HTML   = Inserts a HTML-Code to the Text.
  NO_HTML   = Removes the HTML-Code from the HTML-Text.
  CLEAR     = Clear the document.
  RemoveHdr = delete the Header from the YAM-Mail!!!
  Type      = e.g. Type 2 writes the number 2...
  Space     = Insert a space. (needed for Type)
  EndLine   = Cursorposition to the start of the line.
  StartLine = Cursorposition to the end of the line.
  StartText = To Textstart.
  EndText   = To Textend.

NOT TESTED:

  PRINT     = Print Document.
  MARK      = Mark the line.
  ZD        = Insert Time&Date.
  ClearLine = Delete line at the Cursorposition.
  BEEP      = Alarm.
  Undo      = Undo
  Break     = Stop converting the document.
  Do_Hex    = Converts the text to HEX.
  DO_ASCII  = Converts HEX-Text back to ASCII.
  BlockMark = Mark the next block at the Cursorposition.
  BlockCopy = Copy the marked Block.
  BlockPaste= Insert Block.
  BlockCut  = Delete marked Block.

(AmigaGuide commands:)

  AGIndex   = Insert the Standardbegin for AGuide.
  Node1     = Insert Node.
  EndNode1  = Insert Endnode.
  BGHigh    = Insert Background Highlight. (Cursorposition)
  FGhigh    = Insert Foreground Highlight. (Cursorposition)
  Bold      = To Bold
  Under
  Ital
  UnderBold
  ItalBold
  UnderItalBold
  UnderItal
  AGLink


If you create new Rexxscripts for the TLNG, send it to Pascal!


  Example for a Menuentry Execute Rexx:
  --------------------------------------------

/* Imports text from TLNG 2.20 to CygnusEd4 */
/* CED4io-V1.0 © 03.NOV.2000 by Jochen Grus  */


/* Mark & copy the text to the clipboard */

OPTIONS RESULTS 
TEXTSTART            /* Move the cursor to the top */
MARK                 /* Mark the document */
COPY                 /* copy the marked text to the clipboard */

/* insert now the clipboard to ced */

ADDRESS "rexx_ced"
OPTIONS RESULTS
CEDTOFRONT
PASTE

-------------------------------------------------------------------

You must use ADDRESS "TextLoaderNG_1".

YAM example:

OPTIONS RESULTS 
ADDRESS "TextLoaderNG_1"
PASTE

Clipboard will be inserted to TLNG...

-------------------------------------------------------------------

- RexxManager

  Tool to speak with other programs!
  Don`t run script for the TLNG, use "Execute Arexx-Script" from
  the menu. If you run a TLNG-Script from the Rexx-Manager, it
  will crash the TLNG!!!

  f.g. CygnusEd

  Click twice on Rexx_ced.
  Type Open into the second row and hit Return or click on to
  "Send Arexx command".

- ARexx-Command

  Execute a internal Rexx command.
  See the commands above...

- Execute Rexx-Script

  Execute an internal or external Arexx-Script.
  

- New RTF Loader

- Hmmm there are some more news but i forgot it...

  For more information consult the german guide -
  oh you can`t speak german - doesn`t matter, many
  Germans can`t speak it either...  Hi Helmut!

  Do you want to write a new (complete) guide?

  Do it!!!
  
