@NODE Features "Features (Viehtschaß)"

=======================================
@{bg highlight} Features: @{bg back}
=======================================

@{bg highlight}English:@{bg back}
========

Import Filter for:

- Word 5.0 DOS §   
- Word 6.0 DOS §      
- Word 4.0 DOS §   
- Word 5.0 MAC (Rel1)      
- Word 5.1 MAC (Rel2)      
- Word 6.0 WIN (rel5)     
- Word 7 (rel6)         
  
   * Format will be holded.

     but not, if somebody uses a special keycode.

     TAB`s can`t be set right, because if you take a look with
     a HEX-Editor to the texts you will see only one code for
     the TAB and nothing more. If you create a scalable TAB with
     f.e. Word than the TAB is still a TAB...

     If there was a graphics at the document you will get following
     lines at the picture position:
     
     Inserted picture blabla...

     If a line uses more than 250 characters the TLNG will split this
     line with " - " and will continue at the new line.

     Time to convert: between 10 & 25 seconds (depends on the size of the document)
     (68060)

- Word 8 (MAC&PC) (rel3)          

  * see Word7

     Time to convert: between 10 & 25 seconds (depends on the size of the document)
     (68060)

- MSWorks 5.0     §      
- WordPerfect 5.0 (Rel1)      
- WordPerfect 5.x (Rel1)      
- WordStar 5-7    §       
- RTF (rel1)
- ANSI (rel1)


§ = Tested only with one document that means no guarantee if these
    filters really working... But why not.
   
    I will need two documents with different texts to get the right
    textpositions and codes...

Amiga:
------

- AmigaWriter 1.2 (rel4)   Finished

  * Shit... 

    Sometimes they are using $09 sometimes $0B for the Return
    or the paragraphs and sometimes they using nothing for it.
 
    If a line uses more than 250 characters the TLNG will split this
    line with  a "-" and will continue at the new line.
  
- FinalWriter 5.0 & 97 (rel2)   Finished

  * If there is an character at the start of a line or in a line
    than there was a special attribute...

    Didn`t work with older formats...


- WordWorth 5-7   (rel4)  Finished

  * If there is an character at the start of a line or in a line
    than there was a special attribute...

    If a line uses more than 250 characters the TLNG will split this
    line with  -  and will continue at the new line.

- ProText 5 & 6

  * You can load these documents with the normal LOAD command
    or with the Converter, but than you must delete the first
    10 lines... 
  
(Converter: better format but it takes more time to load the text)

Converter: (rel4)        Finished

- All kind of files/documents can be converted to a normal
  text, that means you will get only the readable part of
  the loaded file and no ˙ţýń etc.

