@NODE Data1 "Convert a document"

To convert a document you should try this first...

Following Formats are recognized:

Word6 (WIN/MAC), Word7 & 8 (WIN&MAC), WordPerfect 5.0 Dos & 5.x, 
FinalWriter (5&97), WordWorth and AmiWriter.

You should select DOS/WIN for Word6 and WordPerfect5 documents
first and if this is not working try the MAC Version.

If there are still strange things happens maybe the document
is a "inserted" format (Excel).

@ENDNODE


@NODE sav1 "Speichern"

ASCII             - Save the text as Ascii
FTXT              - Save the text as FTXT (Clipboard format)
ClipBoard         - Save the text to the Clipboard @{" More Info " Link f1}
HTML              - Save the text as HTML document 
RTF               - Save the text as RTF document
WordWorth7        - Save the text as WordWorth7 document
Overwrite         - Overwrite the old file...

@ENDNODE

@NODE f1 "ClipBoard"

Save the whole document to the clipboards.
You can paste the clips to every other program
which will work with the clipboard format.

(Shortcut: Amiga-v)


@ENDNODE

@NODE f2 "Rexx"

Rexxmodule:

If somebody want to write a new rexx module, it`s only 
important that the program uses cut&paste f.e. WordWorth:

OPTIONS RESULTS           (Result)
ADDRESS "WORDWORTH.1"     (Work with the program (here Wordworth). You will 
                           find the address with programs like Scout or ARTM.
                           On Scout click on Ports to get the addresses.)

PASTE 'ram:clipboards/0'  (The rexx command Paste for WordWorth only)

Every program uses different names for the paste command f.e.

'pastetext' - Rexx command for PageStream


Pageliner:

If you have set the assignments at the user-startup
for Pagestream you don`t must start the PageLiner.

All other programs must be started before you choose
the menuitem and they should use an own Public-Screen
to find the address of the program.



@ENDNODE

