Version 1.14/15  02.04.99
----------------------------------------------

- Added Word6 for MAC filter

- Added "Find classes" to the converter module

- Changed the menu "Converter"

  The subitem "Word 6-8 & Amiga" will replace all
  old subitems of the Word and the Amiga filters.
 
  If you don`t know which kind your document is 
  try first this menuitem.

  If the class/datatype is not supported it will not convert it.

  Supported types are: Word6 (WIN/MAC), Word7 & 8 (WIN), 
                       FinalWriter (5&97), WordWorth & AmiWriter. 

  For all other types you still must use the other subitems, coz
  i didn`t have for these modules text examples to get the right
  type of file. (Like WPerfect,Word for Dos etc.)

- Changed Save menu


Version 1.16  05.04.99
----------------------------------------------

- Menus now font sensetive

- Changed some requesters and the editor window to be
  compatible to VisualPrefs  

  (Requesters will changed in the near future again) 

  Thanks to Marko Seppänen for the bug report

- Removed very ugly bug from converting documents.

  I forgot to set a buffer and with no buffer TLNG quits.

  Thanks to Robin Brookes for the bug report.


Version 1.17-1.20  06.04.99
----------------------------------------------

- Add "Set Editorfont" to the menu.

  At the start TLNG will read your fonts.prefs if the selected font
  is not 11pt and not proportional it will change to Topaz 11.
  With the new menuitem you could change this to a font you like,
  with the limitations above. You should select f.e. XEN or a font
  from the ThinXXX family (f.e Thin711).


